criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Urticaria +/- angioedema present for a minimum of 6 weeks;

          -  Agree to be on anti-histamine prn;

          -  Age older than 8 years old, with no upper age limit;

          -  Causes such as parasite infestation, microbial and viral infections, autoimmune
             disease, or other pathology that could account for the U/A/P should be excluded;

          -  Skin prick test and/or radioallergosorbent (RAST) test are negative for all food
             allergens tested, or patient had achieved no symptomatic improvement after strict
             avoidance of all skin test-positive foods;

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Pregnant or breast feeding women;

          -  Patients who is taking central nervous system (CNS) acting agents (including
             tranquilizers, antidepressants, sedatives, hypnotics or antiepileptics) at any time;
